column3: Fixed comment nit and clarified commit message\n
This (pre-existing) comment is too specific to be correct.\n
Why can't we mark a tx for removal already? It was accepted into the memory pool, so alls its inputs must be satisfied?\n

This tx isn't in the orphan map.   We're just now receiving it off the network and accepting it to the mempool, so it never entered the orphan map.  If it was a duplicate transaction that was an orphan the first time it was received, it would have previously been accepted to the mempool at the time its inputs were satisfied, and wouldn't be accepted here.\n\nIt doesn't hurt to add tx to vEraseQueu
